---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="FAQ - Free Prompt Studio" description="Frequently asked questions about Free Prompt Studio.">
  <h1 class="text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>

  <section class="mt-8 space-y-8 text-sm text-secondary leading-relaxed">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Is it really free?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">Yes. Free, open source, runs in your browser. No signup, no API keys, no charges.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Do you store my prompts?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">No. Everything stays in your browser. Nothing is collected, stored, or transmitted. The only thing saved locally is your theme preference.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">What frameworks are available?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">CO-STAR, RISEN, CRAFT, ORACLE, RACE, CARE, APE, CREATE, TAG, CREO, RISE, PAIN, COAST, and Freeform. Pick one that fits your task.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Which AI models does it target?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Midjourney, Grok, and Perplexity. The output adapts to the model you select.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">How does the analyzer work?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">It scores your prompt across 7 dimensions: clarity, role, constraints, context, examples, tone, and format. Score is 0-100 with suggestions for what to add.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Can I share prompts?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">Yes. Copy to clipboard or share via URL. The prompt is encoded in the URL hash. No server involved, nothing stored.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Does it work offline?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">Yes. Once loaded, everything runs locally. Google Fonts need a connection on first visit.</p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-base font-medium text-primary">Dark mode?</h2>
      <p class="mt-1">Dark mode is the default. Toggle it with the sun/moon icon in the header. Preference is saved locally.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
